how can i get more quota in afs stanford answers stanford university stanford answers how can i get more quota in afs categories accounts and ids administrative applications anti virus and security computer operating systems connecting to the network desktop hardware and support email and calendar help desk restricted information on it services software at stanford stanford hospital and clinics telephones and cable tv unix systems and software web services user login login with your sunet id home how can i get more quota in afs search this site to request more personal afs disk space use the afs space sponsor form use the afs space sponsor form to request additional space allocations if you already have over 1 gb of quota you should use the research disk space request form instead to request more group or department afs disk space submit a helpsu request detailing how much additional space you need and why you need it when you get a full service sunet id you get a stanford unix account that comes with 200 mb of of afs disk space for storing web pages text files computer programs and other forms of electronic information this space is referred to as quota and it can fill up depending on how you use it your afs quota is not the same thing as your email quota to check your personal afs and email quota at the same time log in to stanford unix and at the command prompt type lelandquota to check your group or department afs quota log in to stanford unix use the cd command to get to the group or department directory you want to check and type fs listquota creating and maintaining web pages group class department web pages personal web pages afs openafs and webafs stanford university 450 serra mall stanford california 94305 650 723 2300 terms of use copyright complaints
